content:
Creating a digital clock using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript is a great way to practice your web development skills. Here's a simple example to help you get started:

### HTML

First, create a basic HTML structure with a container for the clock.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Digital Clock</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="clock" id="clock">
        00:00:00
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### CSS

Next, style the clock to make it visually appealing.

```css
/* styles.css */
body {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100vh;
    background-color: #282c34;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
}

.clock {
    font-size: 3em;
    color: #61dafb;
    background-color: #20232a;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}
```

### JavaScript

Finally, use JavaScript to update the clock every second.

```javascript
// script.js
function updateClock() {
    const clockElement = document.getElementById('clock');
    const now = new Date();
    const hours = String(now.getHours()).padStart(2, '0');
    const minutes = String(now.getMinutes()).padStart(2, '0');
    const seconds = String(now.getSeconds()).padStart(2, '0');
    clockElement.textContent = `${hours}:${minutes}:${seconds}`;
}

// Update the clock every second
setInterval(updateClock, 1000);

// Initial call to display the clock immediately
updateClock();
```

### Explanation

1. **HTML**: The `<div>` with the ID `clock` acts as a container for displaying the time.
2. **CSS**: Styles the clock with a centered layout, a readable font size, and some visual enhancements like color, padding, and shadow.
3. **JavaScript**: 
   - `updateClock()` function retrieves the current time, formats it to always have two digits for hours, minutes, and seconds, and updates the clock's display.
   - `setInterval()` is used to call `updateClock()` every 1000 milliseconds (1 second).
   - An initial call to `updateClock()` ensures the clock displays the current time as soon as the page loads.

This setup will create a simple digital clock that updates every second to show the current time. Feel free to modify the styles to suit your design preferences!
